---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout title="Our Story" description="How Jack and Jenna met, fell in love, and got engaged at Haskell's Beach.">

  <div class="section section--wide story-layout">

    <header class="story-header">
      <p class="eyebrow">A love story</p>
      <h1 class="page-heading">Our Story</h1>
    </header>

    <article class="story-body prose">

      <section class="story-chapter">
        <h2 class="chapter-title display">How We Met</h2>
        <p>
          [How you met — add your own details here. Keep it warm and specific; the
          best details are the small, true ones that you'd tell a friend over dinner.]
        </p>
        <p>
          [Continue the story. What was the moment things shifted from "friends" to
          something more? A line or two is plenty.]
        </p>
      </section>

      <div class="story-photo-placeholder" aria-label="Photo placeholder — engagement photo coming soon">
        <span class="display">Photo coming soon</span>
      </div>

      <section class="story-chapter">
        <h2 class="chapter-title display">The Proposal</h2>
        <p>
          On a warm afternoon, we walked the bridge at Haskell's Beach on the way back
          from lunch at the Bacara. The views stretched out over the Pacific, the
          hills were golden behind us &mdash; and that's where Jack asked the question.
        </p>
        <p>
          Jenna said yes.
        </p>
        <p>
          [Feel free to add more color here: what she was wearing, what you said,
          how you felt. Or leave it just like this.]
        </p>
      </section>

      <div class="story-photo-placeholder" aria-label="Photo placeholder — engagement photo coming soon">
        <span class="display">Photo coming soon</span>
      </div>

      <section class="story-chapter">
        <h2 class="chapter-title display">Now &amp; Next</h2>
        <p>
          [A short paragraph about where you are now. Where you live, what you're
          excited about for the wedding and beyond. One or two sentences is great.]
        </p>
        <p>
          We can't wait to celebrate with everyone we love. See you in April 2028.
        </p>
      </section>

    </article>

  </div>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
.story-layout {
  padding-top: var(--s-lg);
  padding-bottom: var(--s-xl);
}

.eyebrow {
  font-size: 0.75rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.18em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--muted);
  margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
}

.story-header {
  margin-bottom: var(--s-lg);
}

.story-body {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: var(--s-lg);
}

.story-chapter {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 1em;
}

.chapter-title {
  font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
  color: var(--accent);
  font-weight: 300;
  font-style: italic;
}

.story-photo-placeholder {
  width: 100%;
  max-width: 640px;
  aspect-ratio: 4 / 3;
  background: oklch(from var(--blush) l c h / 0.2);
  border: 1px dashed oklch(from var(--blush) l c h / 0.5);
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  color: var(--muted);
  font-size: 1.2rem;
  font-style: italic;
}
</style>
